🚀 Task Master v1.0 | Vanilla JS CRUD Application
A high-performance, logic-driven Task Management application built with Pure Vanilla JavaScript. This project focuses on efficient DOM manipulation, state persistence, and a seamless user experience without the need for heavy frameworks.

🔗 Live Demo


🛠 Key Engineering Features
Persistence Engine: Uses localStorage to ensure your tasks stay saved even after closing the browser.
Session Resilience (Draft Mode): Implemented sessionStorage logic to auto-restore unsaved inputs if the page is accidentally refreshed.
Performance Optimized: Utilizes DocumentFragment for DOM rendering to minimize reflows and repaints, ensuring a smooth UI.
Event Delegation: Efficiently handles dynamic elements (Edit/Remove buttons) using a single event listener on the parent container.
Smart Notifications: A custom-built notification system that provides real-time feedback for every action (Add, Edit, Delete, Error).
Clean CRUD Logic: A centralized app object structure to maintain clean, readable, and scalable code.

🏗 Tech Stack
Frontend: HTML5, CSS3 (Modern Flexbox/Grid)
Logic: Vanilla JavaScript (ES6+)
Storage: Web Storage API (localStorage & sessionStorage)

